decrementTokens

public TokenAmount[] decrementTokens(java.lang.String srd,
                                     TokenAmount[] tokenAmounts)
                              throws VindiciaReturnException,
                                     VindiciaServiceException
Performs one or more token transactions on an account. These transactions may be on multiple token types. This method is equivalent to tokenTransaction with a positive value for token amount(s).

Has the following return values:

'401:Balance too low' One or more requested token decrements would drop the user's balance below 0
'404:Token not found' One or more tokens specified is not a saved type; the tokens available on the account are still returned, however.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
tokenAmounts - A set of token amounts to be subtracted from the user's account
Returns:
array of TokenAmount objects - New balances for each changed token
Throws:
VindiciaReturnException - for non-200 return codes from Vindicia
VindiciaServiceException

fetchByPaymentMethod

public static Account[] fetchByPaymentMethod(java.lang.String srd,
                                             PaymentMethod paymentMethod,
                                             int page,
                                             int pageSize)
                                      throws VindiciaReturnException,
                                             VindiciaServiceException
This method will return a list of accounts that have the specified payment method associated with them. The The input PaymentMethod object need not be fully populated. If VID is specified in the input PaymentMethod object, it will be used as the primary identifying factor for the payment method record to be used as the search criterion. If VID is not specified in the input PaymentMethod object, merchantPaymentMethodId will be used as the primary identifying factor for the payment method record to be used as the search criterion. If both VID, and merchantPaymentMethod are absent, account number for a Credit Card, account number - bank routing number combination for ACH/ECP, fiscal number used for a Boleto payment will be used as the search criterion depending on type specified in the input PaymentMethod object. Since PayPal transactions processed through CashBox have no unique identifier, all accounts that use PayPal will be returned. Merchants should use the paging parameters to limit the number of records returned per call

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
paymentMethod - Payment method to use as search criterion
page - Page number to begin results returned. First page number is 0
pageSize - Number of results to display per page, should be more than 0
Returns:
array of Account objects - Array of Account objects matching the search criteria
Throws:
VindiciaReturnException - for non-200 return codes from Vindicia
VindiciaServiceException

transfer

public Account transfer(java.lang.String srd,
                        Account sourceAccount)
                 throws VindiciaReturnException,
                        VindiciaServiceException
Merges target account with a given (source) account and returns the target account with merged contents. Both accounts specified as input to this call must exist in the CashBox system otherwise an error will be returned. This method transfers payment methods, chargebacks, tax exemptions, autobills, activities, token grants and deductions, transactions, and name-value pairs associated with the source account into the target account. Additionally, it creates two name-value pairs with names VIN_MERCHANT_CUSTOMER_ID_UPDATED_FROM and VIN_MERCHANT_CUSTOMER_ID_UPDATED_DATE in each of the autobill object transferred indicating the original merchantCustomerId the autobill was associated with and the date on which it was transferred. The source account is stripped of all of the above contents but will continue to exist in the system with some basic attributes.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
sourceAccount - Account to be merged with the target account
Returns:
Account object - Target account with merged contents of the two input accounts
Throws:
VindiciaReturnException - for non-200 return codes from Vindicia
VindiciaServiceException
